description: "An evocative exhibition by photographer Cao Nguyen Vu, capturing the soul of Ly Son Island - a volcanic
island paradise off Vietnam's central coast. This exhibition showcases the unique geological formations, pristine
beaches, and rich maritime culture that make Ly Son a treasured natural and cultural heritage site.

The collection features breathtaking aerial and landscape photography that reveals the island's dramatic volcanic
terrain, crystal-clear waters, and the daily lives of fishing communities who have called this island home for
generations.

Visitors will discover the spiritual significance of Ly Son's ancient temples, the traditional garlic farming that
sustains the local economy, and the vibrant festivals that celebrate the island's maritime heritage.

The exhibition includes immersive video installations and soundscapes that transport viewers to this remote island
paradise."
